 "redflags": [
  "Output-contract mismatch: the profile block requested plausibility/reasoning_trace keys while the final STRICT OUTPUT CONTRACT requested five different keys; I followed the final explicit contract but noting the divergence.",
  "Rung 5 (functional rescue) is entirely UNTESTED in any Complex I disease model; all supporting rescue data are cross-disease (Friedreich, Parkinson, AMD), so the central claim is inferential.",
  "The CRISPR anchor (PMID 31730859) does NOT place isolated Complex I inhibition in GPX4's synthetic-lethal set \u2014 the author discloses this, but it weakens the direct chain from screen to Complex-I-specific ferroptosis; Rung 3 is explicitly an analogy, not the same genetic operation.",
  "Patient RGC evidence base is very thin (one patient, one carrier, one control in GSE103619), and the RGC-specific tissue-access claim cannot lean on GTEx (no optic-nerve coverage).",
  "Cannot independently re-verify the cited PMIDs/patent numbers/GTEx TPM values from within this assessment; scores assume the identifiers resolve as described, as the author claims live verification.",
  "Rung 5 (functional rescue in a Complex I model) is UNTESTED \u2014 all supporting rescue data is cross-disease (Friedreich, Parkinson, AMD); the central claim rests on analogy until the pilot is run, which the author does state plainly.",
  "The CRISPR anchor screen showed GPX4 as synthetic-lethal with CIII/CV/mtDNA lesions, and isolated Complex I inhibition (piericidin) was NOT in that set \u2014 the Complex-I-specific hit was the NADPH/pentose-phosphate arm. The author discloses this, but it weakens the direct genetic link to Complex I disease more than the enthusiastic framing implies.",
  "Tissue-access argument (low SLC7A11 in nerve/muscle/heart) rests on bulk GTEx mRNA, does not capture cysteine flux or alternative import (EAAT3), and lacks the vulnerable-vs-spared single-cell contrast that would actually support RGC selectivity \u2014 correctly flagged as suggestive-not-dispositive.",
  "The GSE103619 LHON iPSC-RGC resource is a single patient plus one carrier and one control; genuinely isogenic CRISPR-corrected controls would need to be generated, so the proposed 6-8 week timeline may be optimistic if the isogenic line does not already exist.",
  "No numerical estimate of the required deuterated-pool fraction versus achievable membrane incorporation in human RGCs, and dietary PUFA dilution is noted but not quantified \u2014 the sub-stoichiometric threshold claim is cited but not sized for this tissue."
 ],
